import '../styles/main.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>In Production - Chapter 1</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Century+Schoolbook&family=Roboto:wght@400;500&family=EB+Garamond:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body class="dark-mode in-production-background">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" with-base>Home</a> → <a href="/in-production" with-base>In Production</a> → Chapter 1
      </nav>
      
      <h1>In Production - Chapter 1: Deployment & Maintenance</h1>
      
      <div class="content-section implementation-background">
        <h2>The Live Environment</h2>
        <p>
          "By failing to prepare, you are preparing to fail." - Benjamin Franklin
        </p>
        
        <blockquote class="highlight">
          "The plans of the diligent lead to profit as surely as haste leads to poverty." - Proverbs 21:5
        </blockquote>
        
        <p>
          Production deployment is where theory meets reality. Every decision made in design 
          and engineering is tested against real users, real data, and real constraints.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section solution-background">
        <h2>Deployment Strategy</h2>
        <h3>Production Checklist:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Performance optimization and compression</li>
          <li>SSL certificate configuration</li>
          <li>CDN setup for global distribution</li>
          <li>Error monitoring and logging</li>
          <li>Backup and recovery procedures</li>
          <li>Security hardening and audits</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>
          "Measure twice, cut once" applies doubly to production deployments. 
          Every change should be tested, staged, and verified before reaching users.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section experimental-background">
        <h2>Monitoring & Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          "What gets measured gets managed." - Peter Drucker
        </p>
        
        <h3>Key Metrics:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS)</li>
          <li>Error rates and stack traces</li>
          <li>User flow completion rates</li>
          <li>API response times</li>
          <li>Resource utilization</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>
          Like a ship's captain reading the stars, we must constantly monitor 
          our digital vessels to ensure they stay on course.
        </p>
      </div>

      <footer>
        <a href="/in-production" with-base class="back-link">← Back to In Production</a>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
